fense department us energy secretaryedit spencer abraham working as the secretary of energy near yucca mountain abraham was appointed secretary of energy by the incoming george w bushs administration on november   abraham announced that he would resign from this position effective with the swearing in of his successor samuel w bodman on february   in  lebanese ambassador farid abboud awarded abraham the national order of the cedar hoover institutionedit abraham was a distinguished visiting fellow at the hoover institution an influential think tank based at stanford university from  through  after leaving office abraham opened the abraham group a washington dc based international strategic consulting firm in  spencer abraham accepted the appointment as chairman of the board of areva inc the us subsidiary of the french nuclear energy company thompson for presidentedit on july   abraham was announced as an ambassador to official washington in the fred thompson presidential campaign later careeredit in  abraham was appointed nonexecutive chairman of the board of areva inc the american arm of the french nuclear company areva which is planning to build epr nuclear power plants in the united states and is building the mixed oxide fuel mox manufacturing plant at the savannah river site to convert legacy weaponsgrade plutonium into power station fuel with william tucker abraham wrote lights out ten myths about and real solutions to americas energy crisis which was published in july  abraham is also the chairman and ceo of the abraham group a strategic consulting firm providing assistance to clients seeking opportunities in the us and global markets electoral historyedit michigan us senate election  party candidate votes  ± democratic debbie stabenow   republican spencer abraham incumbent   michigan us senate election  party candidate votes  ± republican spencer abraham   democratic bob carr   libertarian jon coon   referencesedit  httppoliticalgraveyardcomgroupeasternorthodo